&lt;p&gt;Grass is a network sharing application that allows users to share their unused bandwidth. Effectively, this is a residential proxy network that directly rewards individual residential IPs for the bandwidth they provide. Grass will route traffic equitably among its network and meter the amount of data that each node provides to fairly distribute rewards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In non-technical terms: Grass unlocks everyone&#39;s ability to earn rewards by simply sharing their unused internet bandwidth on personal devices (laptops, smartphones).&lt;/p&gt;
